CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1953, pg. 2 reads: " ...Leon Smith, 19, of 2332 Wylie Ave.,..., was accused of brining two guns and a blackjack to the fight and of taking the murder knife home, after the killing. Coroner McClelland holds the blackjack and the knife (enclosed in cellophane) over the three guns in the center photo..."
TitMainTitle: Coroner William D. McClelland holding Blackjack and bag with knife over three handguns during inquest of Charles Benson death
